title: warning: unused variable 'RCSrc' [-Wunused-variable] (and several others) while executing `./x.py build && ./x.py install`

labels.name: A-LLVM
labels.description: Area: Code generation parts specific to LLVM. Both correctness bugs and optimization-related issues.

labels.name: T-bootstrap
labels.description: Relevant to the bootstrap subteam: Rust's build system (x.py and src/bootstrap)

body:
While executing `./x.py build && ./x.py install` at this commit hash 4781233a77e879e49cb5ce3c98d2abba6a6ade7a, I got warnings below.

```
[2465/3025] Building CXX object lib/Target/M68k/CMakeFiles/LLVMM68kCodeGen.dir/M68kInstrInfo.cpp.o
/rust/src/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Target/M68k/M68kInstrInfo.cpp:360:15: warning: unused variable 'RCSrc' [-Wunused-variable]
  const auto *RCSrc = TRI.getMaximalPhysRegClass(Src, MVTSrc);
              ^
/rust/src/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Target/M68k/M68kInstrInfo.cpp:406:15: warning: unused variable 'RCSrc' [-Wunused-variable]
  const auto *RCSrc = TRI.getMaximalPhysRegClass(Src, MVTSrc);
              ^
/rust/src/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Target/M68k/M68kInstrInfo.cpp:748:26: warning: unused variable 'MF' [-Wunused-variable]
  const MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent();
                         ^
/rust/src/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Target/M68k/M68kInstrInfo.cpp:763:26: warning: unused variable 'MF' [-Wunused-variable]
  const MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent();
                         ^
4 warnings generated.
[2484/3025] Building CXX object lib/Target/M68k/MCTargetDesc/CMakeFiles/LLVMM68kDesc.dir/M68kMCCodeEmitter.cpp.o
/rust/src/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Target/M68k/MCTargetDesc/M68kMCCodeEmitter.cpp:223:12: warning: unused variable 'Opcode' [-Wunused-variable]
  unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
           ^
/rust/src/llvm-project/llvm/lib/Target/M68k/MCTargetDesc/M68kMCCodeEmitter.cpp:40:22: warning: private field 'MCII' is not used [-Wunused-private-field]
  const MCInstrInfo &MCII;
                     ^
2 warnings generated.
```
